article.headline: Pacific 73, Cal Poly-SLO 63
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Demetrece Young scored 19 points and Terrell Smith added 15 to lead Pacific past Cal Poly 73-63 Friday night. Young scored 13 of his points in the second half. Joe Ford had a double-double with 10 points and 11 rebounds, along with four blocks and a steal. Sam Willard added 10 points for the Tigers (9-5), who dominated the boards with a 32-25 rebounding advantage. Lorenzo Keeler scored 18 points to lead Cal Poly (4-9), and Shawn Lewis had 17. David Hanson came off the bench to add 15 points for the Mustangs. Shawn Lewis hit a 3-pointer 24 seconds into the second half for a 40-35 Cal Poly lead, but Pacific went on a 15-2 run to turn the game around. The Mustangs closed the gap to one point on two occasions, the last at 55-54 with 6:49 remaining on another 3-pointer by Lewis. But the Tigers went on another run, outscoring Cal Poly 12-2 over the next 3 1/2 minutes to pull away for good.
